aphy, Kirsch documents that Auden's faith and his religious doubt were the matrix of his work and life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aChristian biographyxEngland. 0aChristian biographyzEngland. 0aPoets, EnglishxBiographyx20th century. 0aPoets, Englishy20th centuryvBiography. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Literature & the Arts.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300128659423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300128659.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles